# Backend (FastAPI)

The backend is the **only writer-free** view over DuckDB. The trading
engine writes; the backend exposes typed reads.

## Required

- Routers live in `backend/api/routers/<resource>.py`. One resource per file.
- Every endpoint returns a Pydantic response model (`<Resource>Out`).
  Never return raw dicts or ORM rows.
- Repositories are injected via FastAPI `Depends` from `backend/api/deps.py`.
  Routers do not open DB connections directly.
- `GET /api/system/health` returns `{status, version, env, uptime_s, db_ok, redis_ok}`.

## Forbidden

- Mutating endpoints (POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE) that touch trades, strategies,
  signals, or risk state. Mutations belong to the trading engine.
- Calling exchange APIs from a router. The frontend never reaches a venue
  through the backend.
- Importing from `execution/`, `risk/engine.py`, or `research/llm/`.
- Embedding API keys in code or env-default values.

## CORS

Allowed origins come from `BACKEND_ALLOWED_ORIGINS` (comma-separated).
Default in dev: `http://localhost:3000`.

## Errors

Raise `fastapi.HTTPException` with a typed `detail`. Don't swallow
exceptions silently. Repository errors map to 5xx; validation errors to
422 (FastAPI default).

## Tests

`tests/e2e/test_api_app.py` exercises every router via `TestClient`.
A new endpoint without an e2e test fails review.
